[The enhanced recommendation of the use of Tdap is overdue for its
use in limiting the outbreaks of pertussis around the country. One
might also suggest that, for both health care workers and day care
workers involved in the care of not yet fully immunized infants,
immunization should be mandatory. Given the New York State experience
with health care workers, especially nurses, refusing mandatory
epidemic H1N1 vaccination, this may be difficult to enforce. Supreme
Court precedence, however, going back to 1905 (Jacobson v. State of
Massachusetts
<http://biotech.law.lsu.edu/cases/vaccines/Jacobson_v_Massachusetts.htm>)
gives states the power to require vaccinations. - Mod.LL]
